5:
The land of the Oxtans is in worse
shape than I expected, perhaps
even more so than what we saw
with the Swes'...
8:
Oh, it is. It's the area that suffered
the most from the attacks in the
whole kingdom.
12:
And stopping that isn't their top
priority? Damn, these guys are some
real pieces of work.
16:
They must have some very
compelling reason to ignore this...
20:
Let's go, everyone! I need to know
what that reason is!
24:
It seems you had a fruitful
conversation last night.
28:
I just parroted what I had once been
told myself. Thinking back, it's quite
embarrassing.
31:
Don't worry. That's what we all do.
I'm no exception.
34:
Huh, would you listen to that? Guess
you have a cute side too.
39:
F-Father Marden... And Sir Nouin and
Sir Swes too... What brings you here?
42:
I'll get straight to the point. What is it
that you people are doing here?
46:
Look, these are the funds for the
research facility you have here.
Care to explain what this
outrageous amount of money is for?
49:
It's... to research relics. The council
knows that as well. I fail to see the
issue.
51:
And you pay people who don't even
exist for their services. Still failing to
see the issue?
54:
Silence is your answer? Betraying
the Star Augurs must be a scarier
prospect than being suspected of
misappropriating the House's funds.
57:
T-truly, Father, I wonder what you
are talking about...
59:
You are free to keep denying it.
Whether that is a good idea,
however...
61:
If you hope that the main family will
protect you, then your hopes rest on
my brother who is both an idiot and
a fervid follower of the Kweturs.
65:
Sir, you are an Oxtan. A protector of
the Farlan faith...
68:
Trust me when I say thisâ€”we only
wish to protect the citizens from the
catastrophe that is taking place.
70:
The reason I'm here now is because
I feel that your priorities are
elsewhere.
75:
Tell me, then. Why are you
trembling? What are you scared of?
79:
I want to know! I want to understand
you!
87:
I am sorry, Your Highness. We are
out of time.
95:
We can't have him go and hide the
evidence, can we? Let's go!
99:
We should be acting like diplomats,
not bandits!
104:
Y-you fool! I'll know better than to
listen to you again! Forgive me,
House Oxtan!
107: S-stop them! Do whatever it takes!
111:
Hey, looks to me like we're onto
something.
115:
It's clear as day. This place belongs
to the Star Augurs.
119:
That's impressive. You can just tell at
a glance?
123:
Where have I seen these things
before...
127:
Here already? Sheesh, you could've
given us a minute... Here!
131:
That was the last one. Sorry, I wasn't
expectin' this hindrance.
135:
I was. And I was also expecting that
you'd take care of it by the time we
arrived.
138:
N-no... It can't be... Th-they are all...
defeated?!
141:
Both the facility and the monsters
guarding it. Genome soldiers, was it?
That's all Star Augur stuff.
143:
And look at all these monsters. What
the hell were you doing here?
146: I d-don't know! We had no idea!
147:
We just lent this place to the Augurs
like the main family told us to! We
know nothing about any monsters
or anything!
149:
I'm not surprised. You're just the
lizard's tail after all.
152:
You know what they'll say? That
some greedy countryside nobles
went against the main family's
wishes for their own nefarious
purposes.
154:
That's why you only knew as much
as you needed to.
161: Stop it, Marden! There's no need!
165: So... won't you make a deal with us?
168:
Take your anger and despair out on
the Kweturs. In exchange, I'll make
sure your family will have a future.
171:
The Kweturs? Marden, what are you
saying?!
175:
The main Oxtan family forced the
Star Augurs on these poor fools. But
the ladder of responsibility goes one
step higher. Straight to the Kweturs.
177:
Surely you know that House Oxtan,
originally, was just one of the
Kweturs' branches. They've never
stopped licking the boot.
180:
Why, I wonder... Knowing full well
that the Kweturs are this kingdom's
cancer...
188:
Do you know who carried out the
assassination of Princess Etheria
Nialas thirty years ago?
